int __cvmx_error_custom_initialize ( void   ) 

Internal use function.

This function's parameters and processing may change in future SDKs.

Some errors require more complicated error handing functions than the automatically generated functions in cvmx-error-init-*.c. This function replaces these handers with hand coded functions for these special cases.

Returns:
Zero on success, negative on failure.

int __cvmx_error_handle_dfa_err_cp2dbe ( const struct cvmx_error_info *  info  ) 

Internal use function.

This function's parameters and processing may change in future SDKs.

DFA_ERR contains R/W1C bits along with R/W bits. This means that it requires special handling instead of the normal __cvmx_error_display() function.
